          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Produced in the reaction",
                " Ca-48(Pb-206,2N) -> No-252 on",
                " 206PbS of 97 % enrichment in 206Pb, 350 microgram/cm2",
                "thickness. The beam energy 215+-2 MeV.",
                "After passing through the separator, the recoil nuclei",
                "were implanted into the focal plane large DSSSD.",
                " The cross sections of the 2n-evaporation channel",
                " (whereby the 252No isotope was produced) is estimated",
                " ~800 nb."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3SP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 116 He-3 proportional counters placed in a",
                "polyethylene moderator in the form of a regular",
                "octagonal prism (height 630 mm, circumscribed circle",
                "diameter 762 mm). See details in Table I of",
                " APP/BS,14,(4),835,2021.",
                "The single-neutron registration efficiency measured",
                "with 248Cm source is 54.7+-0.1% (nonlinear",
                "least-squares method error). The average neutron",
                "lifetime in the setup is 18.4+-0.2 microsec (exponent",
                "fitting error)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An array of DSSSD detectors inside the vacuum",
                "chamber is represented by a focal plane 128 x 128-strip",
                "detector (100 x 100 mm2 area, 500 micron thickness) and",
                "8 side 16 x 16-strip detectors (50 x 60 mm2 area,",
                "700 micron thickness). For registration of alpha-,",
                "beta-particles, and fission fragments.",
                "Energy resolutions were measured using 8 MeV",
                "alpha-particles as 20 keV and 30 keV for the focal and",
                "side silicon detectors, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 3260 reliable events of 252No spontaneous fission were",
                "found."
              ]
            }
          ],
